result.execSummary:
The defendant Brian Nmi Jacobson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Brian Nmi Jacobson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Brian Nmi Jacobson was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Brian Nmi Jacobson was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Brian Nmi Jacobson was found guilty of Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Brian Nmi Jacobson was found guilty of Disorderly conduct. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. records.addlTxt: Defendant Brian Nmi Jacobson in court with attorney Christopher T. Froelich.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 4:15 PM. Froelich has revised offer that he has just recieved and would like a short recess to discuss resolution. Re-called 4: State recomendation is count 1 dimsissed, count 2 amend to FC ordinance of with find of $500 plus cost. Counts 3, 8, 9, 10 & 11 will be DRI. Plea of G to 4, 6 & 7, place on probation for 3 years, court costs only on count 4, count 7 - $1000 fine plus costs, count 6 $100 fine plus costs, conditions of probation: AODA, absolute sobriety, no possession of alcohol, no entry, FT employment, 200 hours of community service, anger management. State arguing for 3 years and Froelich free to argue on probation time. Court dismisses count 1. Court DRI counts 3, 8, 9, 10 & 11. Court amends count 2 to FC ordinance of DC, defendant pleads NC, court accepts plea and imposes fine of $500 plus costs, take money posted. Defendant pleads NC to counts 4, 6 & 7. Court goes over PLQ with defendant and finds he is freely, voluntairly and intelligently entering his plea, waiving his constitutional rights and right to jury trial, court finds factual basis, accepts plea and adjudges guilty. State makes final argument and asks court to follow joint recommendation and asks for a 3 year probation term. Froelich makes final statement and asks court to follow joint recommendation, but argues for lesser probation term. Jacobson makes statement, remorseful. Court will proceed to sentencing: Count 6 - fine of $100 plus costs, 90 DTP/CO. Counts 4, & 7 - With hold sentence and place on probation for 2 years with condtions of: count 4 - court costs only, count 7 - fine of $1000 plus costs to be paid within the first 90 days of probation. AODA and follow through with all recommendations, no consumption or possession of alcohol, no entry into any bars or taverns, FT employment/schooling with job search and report, 200 hours of community service to be completed within the first year of probation on one count only, must submit DNA sample (expunction rights on DNA given). Appeal, voting and firearm rights given.
Final pre-trial on July 13, 2016 at 03:45 pm.

Defendant Brian Nmi Jacobson in court with attorney Christopher T. Froelich.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 1:03 PM. State recites what agreement is: Count 1 - DRI,  Count 2 - amend ordinance of DC - $300 plus costs, Counts 3 & 4 DRI, Count 6 - plead to as alleged sentence to 60 days FC jail, $100 fine plus costs, Count 7 - 3 years probation, $100 fine plus costs, Count 9 - 3 years probation, costs and remaining counts would be DRI. Froelich - needs to investigate the matter further and some additional discovery was just given, Jacobson is not rejecting the offer, just asking for an adjournment. Court will adjourn, bond will be continued.  Final pre-trial scheduled for July 13, 2016 at 03:45 pm.
Final pre-trial on May 27, 2016 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Brian Nmi Jacobson in court with attorney Christopher T. Froelich.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 2:01 PM. State advised waiver of PH, will be filing the INFO which mirrors, shortly. Froelich has reviewed criminal complaint with his client and waives further reading of it and would like to proceed to PH, which he would like to waive and hands the court waiver of PH. Court goes over form with defendant and finds he is freely and voluntarily waiving his right to a preliminary hearing. Court finds probable cause and binds over for trial. Proceed to ARGN. Froelich waives further reading of the information filed and enters NG pleas to all 11 counts. Court accept pleas. Bond continued.  Final pre-trial scheduled for May 27, 2016 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Brian Nmi Jacobson in court.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:40 AM. Jacobson has complaint. Court reads charges and penalties and right to attorney and court appointed attorney. Jacobson understands charges and penalties, wants an attorney, will hire his own (Christopher Froelich) and asks for an AIA. Court continues bond, sets for AIA. Court has noticed the attorney and should move 15CF175 to same date. Froelich to inform Court if he is not available that day.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for February 15, 2016 at 01:00 pm.
